OL,3,C'What would the world be like without
OL,4,Ca war?': Vivid memories of VE Day
OL,6,F"This has all come to an end. What
OL,7,Fwould the world be like without a war?"
OL,9,FMary's first thoughts when she heard
OL,10,Fwar had ended were about her brother
OL,11,Fwho was serving overseas.
OL,13,FShe said: "He was training to be a
OL,14,Fpilot in the RAF and my sort of
OL,15,Freaction was 'is he coming back then
OL,16,Fmum', because I was very fond of him
OL,17,Fyou know. And she said 'oh yes, yes'
OL,18,Fand I thought 'oh I'm happy then'."
