OL,3,C'What would the world be like without
OL,4,Ca war?': Vivid memories of VE Day
OL,6,F"It was just general excitement.
OL,7,FNobody was doing anything logical, it
OL,8,Fwas just mad. Anyway we stayed around
OL,9,Ffor quite a while, we saw the Royal
OL,10,FFamily and Churchill on the balcony.
OL,12,F"I remember thinking isn't it funny
OL,13,Fhow tiny they are because we were such
OL,14,Fa long way away, but it was an
OL,15,Fexperience. It was the first time I'd
OL,16,Fever done that.
OL,18,FMeanwhile, Mary went to the centre of
OL,19,FBournemouth with her mother and
OL,20,Fgrandparents and felt everything was a
OL,21,Fbit out of control.
