OL,3,C'What would the world be like without
OL,4,Ca war?': Vivid memories of VE Day
OL,6,F"It was a very strange deep
OL,7,Fexperience. It's one of those
OL,8,Fexperiences you have in life that you
OL,9,Ffeel them really intensely and you
OL,10,Fnever ever forget them.
OL,12,F"There are certain things during the
OL,13,Fwar that I shall never ever forget."
OL,15,FThe end of the war meant no more bombs
OL,16,Fand blackouts, but rationing and
OL,17,Fausterity continued as Joan and Mary
OL,18,Fgot used to peace.
